{"parse":{"title":"Association for the Recovery of Historical Memory","pageid":8595689,"revid":824400282,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">\"ARMH\" redirects here. For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/ARMH_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-disambig\" title=\"ARMH (disambiguation)\">ARMH (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg/220px-Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg/330px-Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg/440px-Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2448\" data-file-height=\"3264\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Exhumaci%C3%B3n_ARMH.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Excavation of a mass grave by ARMH</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Association for the Recovery of Historical Memory</b> (<b>Asociaci\u00f3n para la Recuperaci\u00f3n de la Memoria Hist\u00f3rica </b> or <b>ARMH</b> in <a href=\"/wiki/Spanish_language\" title=\"Spanish language\">Spanish</a>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Spain\" title=\"Spain\">Spanish</a> organization that collects the oral and written testimonies about the <a href=\"/wiki/White_Terror_(Spain)\" title=\"White Terror (Spain)\">White Terror</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Francisco_Franco\" title=\"Francisco Franco\">Francisco Franco</a> and excavates and identifies their bodies that were often dumped in <a href=\"/wiki/Mass_grave\" title=\"Mass grave\">mass graves</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Emilio Silva and Santiago Macias founded the ARMH in December 2000.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is a group of about 50 Spanish <a href=\"/wiki/Archaeologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archaeologist\">archaeologists</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Anthropologist\" title=\"Anthropologist\">anthropologists</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Forensics\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Forensics\">forensic</a> scientists. The group tries to identify the places of execution through records and interviewing the locals. Sometimes they also receive anonymous information about them.\n</p><p>Volunteer group members gather in a decided place to excavate the mass grave found. They try to exhume the bodies and identify the remains of the victims with <a href=\"/wiki/DNA_test\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"DNA test\">DNA tests</a> and other forensic methods. As of September 2006, ARMH had conducted 40 excavations and found remains of 520 victims.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>As of October 2009 the group had identified the remains of 1.700 victims.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>One of these mass graves outside of <a href=\"/wiki/Burgos\" title=\"Burgos\">Burgos</a> was the subject of a photo-documentary entitled <i>Dark is the Room Where We Sleep</i> at the <a href=\"/wiki/International_Center_Of_Photography\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"International Center Of Photography\">International Center Of Photography</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/New_York,_New_York\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York, New York\">New York, New York</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The current Spanish government refuses to open the historical archives that would allow experts and historians to throw light on the fate of victims of the <a href=\"/wiki/Francoist_State\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Francoist State\">Francoist State</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Association_for_the_Recovery_of_Historical_Memory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Red_Terror_(Spain)\" title=\"Red Terror (Spain)\">Red Terror (Spain)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/General_Archive_of_the_Spanish_Civil_War\" title=\"General Archive of the Spanish Civil War\">General Archive of the Spanish Civil War</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Law_of_Historical_Memory\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Law of Historical Memory\">Law of Historical Memory</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Association_for_the_Recovery_of_Historical_Memory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Preston\" title=\"Paul Preston\">Preston, Paul</a>. <i>The Spanish Civil War. Reaction, Revolution &amp; revenge.</i> Harper Perennial. London. 2006. p.316</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Graham, Helen. <i>The Spanish Civil War. A very Short introduction.</i> Oxford University Press. 2005. p.142</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Elkin, Mike - \"<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.archaeology.org/0609/abstracts/franco.html\">Opening Franco's Graves</a>\" (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Archaeology_(magazine)\" title=\"Archaeology (magazine)\">Archaeology</a>,</i> September/October 2006)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Associated Press <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5jwMqZMBFgUT-1WovIPfURB5871swD9B5288O1\">https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5jwMqZMBFgUT-1WovIPfURB5871swD9B5288O1</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.icp.org/site/c.dnJGKJNsFqG/b.2876525/k.9FC1/Francesc_Torres.htm\">Francesc Torres - International Center Of Photography</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20071111195417/http://www.icp.org/site/c.dnJGKJNsFqG/b.2876525/k.9FC1/Francesc_Torres.htm\">Archived</a> November 11, 2007, at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.elmundo.es/espana/2015/03/30/55184e5eca47417a068b4583.html?cid=SMBOSO25301&amp;s_kw=facebook\">Los historiadores, contra Margallo por negarse a abrir los archivos</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Association_for_the_Recovery_of_Historical_Memory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=